Description: Two papyrus fragments. One is bearing 3 lines of Coptic text written along the fibres (recto), the other is bearing one line, also along the fibres (recto). Mounted with EA 10128, 1013102, 10134, 10136-9.
Curator's comments: Register says 'Found in some tombs in the hills behind Assiut'. Under study by Alain Delattre with a view to publication (updated March 2017).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380882) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380882)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Rev Dr Gulian Lansing
